org.vast.ogc.xlink

Class CachedReference<TargetType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.vast.ogc.xlink.CachedReference<TargetType>
  • Type Parameters:
    TargetType - Type of the link target object

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IXlinkReference<TargetType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefinitionRef, FeatureRef

    public class CachedReference<TargetType>
extends Object
implements IXlinkReference<TargetType>

    Implementation of Xlink Reference that keeps a cached version of the target. Object is cached on the first call to getTarget(). Reloading the target object can be enforced by calling refresh().

    Since:
    Sep 28, 2012
    Author:
    Alex Robin
